-- Osborne's New Bank Tax to Raise $4.5 Billion, Sunday Times Report Says
-- Paul Dobson
-- 2010-06-20T09:14:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-20/osborne-s-new-bank-tax-to-raise-4-5-billion-sunday-times-report-says.html

          
          
             U.K. Chancellor of the Exchequer
 George Osborne  will announce a bank tax in two days aiming to
raise 3 billion pounds ($4.5 billion), the  Sunday Times 
reported, without saying where it got the information.  
 The tax will be based on banksâ€™ balance sheets rather than
their earnings, the newspaper said.  
 Osborne will also proceed with a plan to levy a capital-
gains tax at around 40 percent on non-business assets and will
soften corporation tax when he announces his budget plans, the
Sunday Times reported.  
